NIGERIAN singer Oluwafemi Oladapo aka Slimcase has advised his colleagues in the industry not to hesitate to rebuke devourers in their midst. The music star disclosed this in a recent Instagram live while reacting to American R&B singer R-Kelly’s 30 years sentence following his sex trafficking conviction.   AVRS, NCC meet stakeholders in Lagos     All eyes are on Nigeria, we must do better, says Sleek     The Ibeji Live Experience returns to Terra Kulture on July…   Slimcase revealed how he was a big fan of R-Kelly while growing up and expressed displeasure at the sexual offenses. The singer also warned his colleagues to be careful saying, “You got to be careful, behind every gift there is a curse, so make sure you are rebuking devourers, they are devourers out there bro. That’s how they got Micheal Jackson you know so have something that you do that rebukes devourers spiritually, they are devourers out there bro. You can be your own devourer from an inherited curse from your family, you have to be very careful.”